  "id": "019cfb0b-3cc2-7f20-afd0-61a3e13a36c6",
  "content": "## 03_run_sam2.py — Implementation Complete\n\nPhase 3 SAM2 subject tracking script implemented at `scripts/03_run_sam2.py`. Key design decisions:\n\n### Architecture\n- Single-file implementation following 01_extract_frames.py and 02_claude_scene_analysis.py patterns (workspace root resolution, config loading, logging format)\n- Model loaded once for all clips, unloaded in a `finally` block to guarantee cleanup\n- Each subject tracked independently (one SAM2 session per subject per clip)\n\n### Frame Extraction Strategy\n- Uses ffmpeg to extract ALL frames from source video at full resolution to a temp directory\n- SAM2 `init_state()` receives the frame directory path (supports both .mp4 and JPEG dirs)\n- Frames named 0-indexed (`000000.jpg`, `000001.jpg`, ...) as SAM2 expects\n- Temp directory auto-cleaned after each clip via `tempfile.TemporaryDirectory`\n- Does NOT use Phase 1 keyframes (those are 1280px downscaled for analysis only)\n\n### Frame Number Mapping\n- Scene analysis frame numbers are 1-indexed (from ffmpeg `frame_NNNNNN` naming where `frame_000001` is first)\n- SAM2 frame directory is 0-indexed (`000000.jpg` is first frame)\n- Conversion: scene analysis frame N → SAM2 frame index N-1\n- Output mask naming uses 1-indexed to match source footage: `frame_000001.png`\n\n### SAM2 API Usage\n- `build_sam2_video_predictor(config_file, ckpt_path, device)` for model loading\n- Config name mapping: `sam2_small` → `\"sam2.1_hiera_s\"`, etc.\n- `init_state(video_path=frame_dir, offload_video_to_cpu=True)` — offload to CPU to save VRAM on 6GB card\n- `add_new_points_or_box(state, frame_idx, obj_id=1, box=bbox_pixel)` — pixel coordinates with `normalize_coords=True` (default)\n- `propagate_in_video(state)` yields `(frame_idx, obj_ids, video_res_masks)` — masks are logits, thresholded at 0.0\n- `reset_state(state)` between subjects to free memory\n- Wrapped in `torch.inference_mode()` + `torch.autocast(\"cuda\", dtype=torch.bfloat16)`\n\n### Bounding Box Handling\n- Phase 2 provides normalised [x_min, y_min, x_max, y_max] in 0-1 range\n- Converted to pixel coordinates by multiplying by video width/height\n- SAM2's `normalize_coords=True` (default) expects pixel coordinates and internally divides by video dimensions\n\n### Subject Exit/Re-entry Detection\n- Exit: mask area fraction drops below 0.05% of frame area (`MASK_EXIT_THRESHOLD = 0.0005`)\n- After 30 consecutive empty frames (`EXIT_FRAME_GAP = 30`), subject declared exited\n- Exited frames padded with all-black (empty) masks\n- Re-entry: if mask area recovers after exit, logged and tracking continues\n- Full re-entry with new SAM2 session deferred (current propagation handles many cases)\n\n### VRAM Management\n- Model loaded once via `load_sam2_model()`, logs VRAM before/after\n- `offload_video_to_cpu=True` in `init_state()` reduces VRAM usage\n- Model unloaded via `unload_sam2_model()` with `torch.cuda.empty_cache()`\n- Unload in `finally` block guarantees cleanup even on errors\n\n### Output Format\n- Binary alpha mask: single-channel PNG, 0 (background) or 255 (subject)\n- Path: `working/masks/{clip_id}/{subject_label}/frame_NNNNNN.png`\n- One subdirectory per subject per clip\n\n### Error Handling\n- No scene_analysis files: exit with error pointing to Phase 2\n- No subjects in a clip: skip with info log\n- Source video not found: log error and continue\n- SAM2 failure on a subject: log error with traceback and continue with remaining subjects\n- Model weights missing: exit with clear error and download URL\n- CUDA not available: exit with clear error\n\n### Config Keys Used\n- `sam2_model` (default: sam2_small)\n- `sam2_weights` (default: models/sam2/sam2.1_hiera_small.pt)\n- `gpu_device` (default: cuda:0)\n- `footage_raw`, `footage_flat`, `working_dir`\n\n### Dependencies\n- PyYAML, torch, sam2, numpy, Pillow, ffmpeg (system), ffprobe (system)\n- cv2 NOT used (ffmpeg handles frame extraction more reliably)",
